silver fern
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:ponga, <i>Cyathea dealbata</i>, a tree fern with fronds that are white on the underside, recognised as one of New Zealand's national symbols.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
